  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "To determine the probability of drawing **four white balls** consecutively from a bag containing **5 white, 7 red, and 8 black balls** (total of **20 balls**), we'll follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Understand the Total Number of Balls\n- **White balls (W):** 5\n- **Red balls (R):** 7\n- **Black balls (B):** 8\n- **Total balls:** \\( 5 + 7 + 8 = 20 \\)\n\n### 2. Calculate the Probability Step-by-Step\nSince the balls are drawn **without replacement**, the probability changes with each draw.\n\n1. **First draw (W):**\n   \\[\n   \\frac{5}{20} = \\frac{1}{4}\n   \\]\n   \n2. **Second draw (W):**\n   \\[\n   \\frac{4}{19}\n   \\]\n   \n3. **Third draw (W):**\n   \\[\n   \\frac{3}{18} = \\frac{1}{6}\n   \\]\n   \n4. **Fourth draw (W):**\n   \\[\n   \\frac{2}{17}\n   \\]\n   \n### 3. Multiply the Probabilities\n\\[\n\\text{Probability} = \\frac{5}{20} \\times \\frac{4}{19} \\times \\frac{3}{18} \\times \\frac{2}{17} = \\frac{5 \\times 4 \\times 3 \\times 2}{20 \\times 19 \\times 18 \\times 17}\n\\]\n\nSimplifying:\n\\[\n\\frac{120}{116280} = \\frac{1}{969}\n\\]\n\n### 4. Alternative Approach Using Combinations\nAlternatively, you can use combinations to find the probability:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Probability} = \\frac{\\binom{5}{4}}{\\binom{20}{4}} = \\frac{5}{4845} = \\frac{1}{969}\n\\]\n\n### **Final Answer**\nThe probability of drawing four white balls is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{\\dfrac{1}{969}}\n\\]",
